olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet Brown Mustard Seeds
2 clove garlic
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 packet Onion Chutney
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet mayonnaise

• Cut potato into fries.
• Set your air fryer to 200°C. Place fries into the air fryer basket, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and sprinkle over brown mustard seeds and toss to coat. Cook for 10 minutes. Shake the basket, then cook until golden, a further 10-15 minutes. Divide between serving plates.

TIP: No air fryer? Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Place fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and sprinkle over brown mustard seeds and toss to coat. Bake until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• Finely chop garlic.
• Roughly chop tomato and slice cucumber into rounds.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince, Mumbai spice blend, chicken-style stock powder, fine breadcrumbs, garlic and the egg.
• Using damp hands, shape heaped spoonfuls of the beef mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per person). Transfer to a plate.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook meatballs, turning, until browned and cooked through,
8-10 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove the pan from heat, then add onion chutney and a splash of water, tossing meatballs to coat.

• Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, tomato, cucumber, a pinch of salt and pepper and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil.

• Divide Mumbai beef rissoles, spiced fries and mixed salad between plates.
• Serve with mayonnaise. Enjoy!